cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.DS 

This paper deals with the acceleration of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) by pruning filters that have a small effect on output accuracy. This topic falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) as it involves optimizing the performance of deep learning models. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of BLAS libraries for dense matrix multiplications, which relates to numerical analysis (cs.NA). The paper also presents experimental results on CIFAR10, which is a commonly used dataset in computer vision research, further supporting the classification under cs.CV. Finally, the paper involves the use of pruning techniques, which is a common topic in data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
